    • Method Detail

      • applyFilter

        public boolean applyFilter(java.lang.Object obj)
        Description copied from interface: com.guidewire.pl.system.filters.BeanBasedQueryFilter
        Tells whether or not to include this object in the list. This method will only be called in the case of a beans-table (as oppose to queryRows table). Advice: If you implement this interface, and you think that your class will only be used in a queryRows situation, than make this method throw a NotImplementedException.
        Parameters:
        obj - the object to examine
        Returns:
        true if this object should be shown, false if it should be filtered out
